snippet.textDisplay:
As someone with a peanut allergy who would really like to be able to travel without dying. GET RID OF PEANUTS ON PLANES PLEASE
You can literally have them all you want at home but if you eat them on the plane, folks who are allergic aren't safe to fly! The partials from peanuts can stay on the seat, the arm rests, the tray, the window, the pockets and the planes aren't cleaned regularly. Your peanut dust will sit on that plane for weeks!
I've been turned away from my flight before because the airline didn't want the risk of allergies on board.
Seriously I know it was just a bit, but I'd really like folks to understand how stressful it is also.
